Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Dietary \Di"et*a*ry\, a. Pertaining to diet, or to the rules of diet. [1913 Webster]

Dictionary.Name: The Collaborative International Dictionary of English v.0.44

Definition.WordDefinition: Dietary \Di"et*a*ry\, n.; pl. {Dietaries}. A rule of diet; a fixed allowance of food, as in workhouse, prison, etc. [1913 Webster]
dietary adj : of or relating to the diet; "dietary restrictions" [syn: {dietetic}, {dietetical}] n : a regulated daily food allowance
